- It was released in 1928, a period when cinema was transitioning from silent to sound.
- It stars Thomas Meighan and Evelyn Brent, who were actors in early Hollywood.
- The film has an English intertitle and was produced by Howard Hughes, known for his involvement in the American film industry during that era.
- It deals with themes relevant to the post-World War I period in America, such as societal changes affecting men and women.
